steps.html_instructions: Head east on Cadillac Square toward Bates St
Take the 2nd right onto Randolph Street

Turn right onto M-10 N/Jefferson Ave
Continue to follow M-10 N
Take exit 2A for I-75 toward Toledo/Flint
Keep left at the fork, follow signs for I-75 S/Toledo

Keep left at the fork, follow signs for I-75 S/Toledo and merge onto I-75 S
Entering Ohio
Take exit 204 for I-475 W toward US-23/Maumee/Ann Arbor
Continue onto I-475 W
Take exit 4 for US-24 toward Maumee/Napoleon
Keep right at the fork, follow signs for US-24 W/Napoleon/Waterville and merge onto US-24 W

Continue onto US-24 W
Entering Indiana
Turn left onto the I-469 S/US 30 E/US 24 W ramp

Merge onto I-469 S/U.S. 30 E
Continue to follow I-469 S
Continue onto Lafayette Center Rd
Take exit 0A to merge onto I-69 S toward Indianapolis
Take exit 0-200 for I-465 S/I-465 W/IN-37
Keep left at the fork, follow signs for I-465 S/IN-37 and merge onto I-465 S/IN-37 S
Take exit 44 for I-70 E/I-70 W toward Dayton/Indianapolis
Keep left at the fork, follow signs for I-70 W/Indianapolis
Keep right at the fork, follow signs for Interstate 70 W/Indianapolis and merge onto I-70 W

Keep right at the fork to stay on I-70 W, follow signs for Interstate 70 W/Airport/St Louis
Entering Illinois
Keep left at the fork to continue on I-57, follow signs for Interstate 57 S/Memphis

Keep right at the fork to continue on I-57 S, follow signs for Interstate 57 S/Memphis
Entering Missouri

Take exit 1A to merge onto I-55 S toward Memphis
Entering Arkansas
Take exit 8 to merge onto I-40 W toward Little Rock
Keep left at the fork to continue on I-30 W
Take exit 139B for I-630
Continue onto I-630 W
Take exit 2B for Doctor Martin Luther King Junior Drive

Turn right onto Dr Martin Luther King Dr/M L King (signs for State Capitol Complex)
Continue to follow Dr Martin Luther King Dr
Turn left onto W 7th St
Turn right onto State Capitol
Slight right to stay on State Capitol
